SOLUTION:
The idea is to use a sliding window to keep track of the current count of requests that are greater than 100. We can use a variable to keep track of the maximum count seen so far. We can use a for loop to iterate over the array r. If the current element is greater than 100, we increment the count variable. Otherwise, we reset the count variable to 0. We update the maximum count seen so far by taking the maximum of the current count and the maximum count seen so far.

The time complexity of this solution is O(n), where n is the length of the array r.
"""

from sys import stdin

def main():
    n = int(stdin.readline())
    r = list(map(int, stdin.readline().split()))
    count = 0
    maxCount = 0
    for i in r:
        if i > 100:
            count += 1
        else:
            count = 0
        if count > maxCount:
            maxCount = count
    print(maxCount)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    main()
